    <div class="hero-text">
      <h2>The Challenge</h2>
      <p>Many parents struggle to stay active due to personal, social, and environmental barriers. This page explores the issue using the Social-Ecological Model and proposes practical, family-friendly solutions.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>üîç Barriers to Physical Activity</h2>
    <div class="barriers">
      <div class="card"><strong>Individual:</strong> Fatigue, low motivation, time constraints.</div>
      <div class="card"><strong>Interpersonal:</strong> Lack of support, childcare responsibilities.</div>
      <div class="card"><strong>Organizational:</strong> Inflexible work schedules, no wellness programs.</div>
      <div class="card"><strong>Community:</strong> Unsafe areas, lack of facilities.</div>
      <div class="card"><strong>Policy Advocacy:</strong> Limited funding and lack of incentives.</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>üí° Solutions: Active Families Framework</h2>
    <div class="solutions">
      <div class="card"><strong>Home Workouts:</strong> Free digital routines for busy parents.</div>
      <div class="card"><strong>Support Groups:</strong> Online communities for motivation.</div>
      <div class="card"><strong>Employer Partnerships:</strong> Wellness incentives and flexible hours.</div>
      <div class="card"><strong>Community Events:</strong> Free family fitness days in parks.</div>
      <div class="card"><strong>Policy Advocacy:</strong> Campaigns for funding and incentives.</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>üí∞ Funding Strategy</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Local Grants:</strong> Support community events and instructors.</li>
      <li><strong>NHS/Public Health:</strong> Preventative health programs.</li>
      <li><strong>Corporate Sponsors:</strong> Branded challenges and gym discounts.</li>
      <li><strong>Crowdfunding:</strong> Launch apps and awareness campaigns.</li>
      <li><strong>University Research:</strong> Pilot and evaluate interventions.</li>
    </ul>
